Aggregate Functions

An aggregate function performs a calculation on a set of values in Data Cloud and returns a single value.

Use at least one aggregate function when you define the calculated insights SQL statement. You can use only numeric measures with an aggregate function. A count function supports date, text, and boolean measures.

AGGREGATE	DESCRIPTION	COMMENT
SUM()	Returns the sum of values of a group.	—
MIN()	Returns the minimum value.	—
MAX()	Returns the maximum value.	—
COUNT()	Returns the count.	Count(*) not supported
AVG()	Returns the average.	—
MEAN()	Returns the mean.	—
StdDev()	Returns the standard deviation.	—
Example

In this example, the SUM aggregate calculates the total order amount by an individual.

SELECT
SUM(SALESORDER__dlm.grand_total_amount__c) as TotalOrderAmount__c,
Individual__dlm.Id__c as CustomerID__c
FROM SALESORDER__dlm
LEFT JOIN Individual__dlm ON SALESORDER__dlm.partyid__c = Individual__dlm.Id__c
GROUP BY CustomerID__c
